node.text:
GUIDED READING TOOLKIT 🧰 It’s been over a year since I’ve released this toolkit and it makes me so happy every time I get a message from one of you saying how much easier your guided reading setup is 🥰

This toolkit is designed to help develop your students reading comprehension skills through a variety of targeted activities. 

There are task boxes for:
★ Character Work
★ Setting
★ Story Structure
★ Author Work
★ Vocabulary
★ Character Traits
★ Before Reading
★ Nonfiction Texts
★ Higher Order Thinking
★ Making Predications
★ Inferring
★ Summarizing
★ Determining Importance
★ Visualizing
★ Synthesizing
★ Asking Questions
★ Nouns, Adjectives and Verbs
★ Adverbs and other Parts of Speech

The link is in my profile if you’d like to check it out 💗

📸 @misspickett_

Photo by My Teaching Pal on August 19, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Making Predictions Which character do you think will be most important to the story? Why? The Setting How would the story be different if it were set 1000 years ago? Character Work Choose a character. How would the story be different if this character didn't exist? Author Work Write a letter to the author telling them what parts of the book they should change. Vocabulary Find 5 boring words from the text and replace them with interesting words. Higher Order Choose a character. If you had to buy them a birthday present, what would it be and why?'.

node.text:
ALPHABET BOOKS 🍎These cute, little half-page books will help your students learn all things related to the alphabet 🤩 

In a compact little book, they will have the opportunity to:

⭐️ Read words with specific beginning sounds
⭐️ Trace lowercase and uppercase letters
⭐️ Identify letters
⭐️ Identify beginning sounds

If you’d like to check them out, the link is in my profile 💗

I love the idea of bringing I SPY 👀 into the classroom with these fun worksheets #bestchildhoodgame

I’ve created a fun I SPY bundle that includes worksheets to help students with letter identification, number identification, shape identification and beginning sounds. Makes me so happy to hear how much your students have been loving them so far 🥰

If you’d like to check it out, the link is in my profile 💗

node.text: There are just those things in life that never seem to change #teacherlife #ownit

GROWING BUNDLE OF DECODABLE READERS 📚 I have just released a huge growing bundle of readers, and it is 75% off!!

Once complete, the bundle will include readers for:
⭐️ Short Vowels (AVAILABLE NOW)
⭐️ Long Vowels (coming soon)
⭐️ Digraphs (coming soon)
⭐️ Blends (coming soon)
⭐️ R-Controlled Vowels (coming soon)
⭐️ Diphthongs (coming soon)

You will get access to all these readers as I add a new set every 2-3 weeks. You will not be required to pay anything further 💗

Every reader comes in 2 levels to help you with differentiation. Level 1 readers have less text, are more patterned and have fewer sight words. Level 2 readers have more text, are less patterned and are sight word heavy.

All the short vowel readers shown in this post are in the bundle now and available for you to download and print! The other readers will be coming soon.

If you’d like to know more, check out my story for more details.

The link is in my profile 💗

CLASSROOM DECOR 🎨
I created this beautiful set of minimalist posters a while back, and it still makes me so happy 🥰

This poster set will add a gorgeous pop of color to your classroom. It includes 2 styles – one in complete watercolor (swipe to the end to see this version) and the other is an ink-friendly paper lines version. Both look beautiful displayed and will complement your classroom, whether you want your décor to be bright and colorful or pretty and minimalistic. 

The pack includes:
⭐️ 26 Alphabet Posters
⭐️ 20 Number Posters (to 20)
⭐️ 11 Color Posters
⭐️ 18 Shape Posters

I’ll add the link in my profile if you’d like to check it out 💗

node.text:
BACK TO SCHOOL FOR SECOND GRADE 🎒 It’s nearly back to school time and your second graders will love completing this booklet during their first week of school. It is a multi-functional booklet that is designed to help you get to know your students, to help your students get to know each other and to allow your students to review all the wonderful things they learned in first grade. 

There are 36 pages included!! I’ll add the link in my profile if you’d like to check it out.

P.S. I have a first grade version too! If you’d like the link for this, let me know 💗

BUILD A SENTENCE 🔨👷 This sentence building literacy center is a fun (and sometimes hilarious) way to have your students build high quality sentences. Each of the sentences include pronouns, adjectives, nouns, verbs, adverbs and prepositional phrases. It will provide them with the opportunity to ‘play’ with words and see how specific words can add and change the meaning of a sentence.

This activity will help your students learn about:
⭐️ Sentence structure 
⭐️ How adjectives and adverbs can influence the meaning of a sentence

I’ve listed it as 50% off for 24 hours. The link is in my profile 💗

node.text:
PHONICS, PHONICS, PHONICS!! 🍎 Something big has just landed, and it is 50% off for the next 48 hours!

This big bundle of phonics worksheets includes a set of 6 different worksheets that each come in options for:

⭐️ Short Vowels
⭐️ Long Vowels
⭐️ Digraphs
⭐️ Blends
⭐️ Trigraphs
⭐️ Double Consonants
⭐️ R-Controlled Vowels
⭐️ Diphthongs

There are 492 pages altogether!! They are great to use as a supplement to your phonics programs and will help your students refine and gain skills with decoding, spelling and identifying words with different phonics sounds.

Check out my story for a closer look 👀 All of these packets are available to purchase individually too. If you’d like me to send you an individual link, just send me a DM 😊

The link is in my profile. 50% off for 48 hours 💗

Swipe across to see all the sheets in action!!
